        624,
        0
      ],
      "id": "d275094f-34ad-49e1-91f1-21f71ad20ece",
      "name": "03 - IF WF01 Approved?"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "Analyze this User Story and produce a minimal technical design.\n\nTitle:\n{{ $json.title }}\n\nDescription:\n{{ $json.description }}\n\nAcceptance Criteria:\n{{ $json.acceptance_criteria }}\n\nProject goal:\nMinimal local Python macro calculator.\n\nAllowed scope:\n- simple Python functions\n- pytest\n- local invented nutrition data\n\nAllowed files:\n- macro_calculator.py\n- sample_data.py\n- tests/test_macro_calculator.py\n- requirements.txt\n\nForbidden:\n- FastAPI\n- APIs\n- users\n- auth\n- database\n- SQLAlchemy\n- Docker\n- frontend\n- microservices\n\nReturn ONLY valid JSON.\n\nSchema:\n\n{\n  \"technical_design\": {\n    \"architecture_summary\": \"string\",\n    \"project_structure\": [\"string\"],\n    \"components\": [\"string\"],\n    \"api_endpoints\": [\"No API endpoints required\"],\n    \"services\": [\"No services required\"],\n    \"database_requirements\": [\"No database required\"],\n    \"docker_requirements\": [\"No Docker required\"],\n    \"ci_cd_requirements\": [\"Run pytest only\"],\n    \"testing_strategy\": [\"string\"],\n    \"dependencies\": [\"pytest\"],\n    \"technical_risks\": [\"No major technical risk\"],\n    \"implementation_notes\": [\"string\"]\n  },\n  \"quality_gate\": {\n    \"passed\": true,\n    \"blocking_issues\": [],\n    \"recommendation\": \"CONTINUE\"\n  },\n  \"next_workflow\": \"WF03\"\n}",
        "options": {
          "systemMessage": "=You are a senior software architect inside an AI Software Factory.\n\nApplication scope:\nMinimal local Python macro calculator.\n\nAllowed:\n- simple Python functions\n- pytest\n- local invented nutrition data\n\nForbidden:\n- FastAPI\n- APIs\n- users\n- authentication\n- database\n- SQLAlchemy\n- Docker\n- frontend\n- microservices\n\nAllowed files:\n- macro_calculator.py\n- sample_data.py\n- tests/test_macro_calculator.py\n- requirements.txt\n\nCritical JSON rules:\n- Return ONLY valid JSON\n- No markdown\n- No explanations\n- No comments\n- No trailing commas\n- Arrays must contain strings only\n- Output must be parseable by JSON.parse()\n\nYou must never change the workflow payload structure."
        }
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent",
